{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"FPGOIfZj4F6lT1ANrKWdX","title":"CWF Simulation Study","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"motivation":{"type":"header","text":"Motivation","value":"motivation","line":10,"column":0},"experiment-1":{"type":"header","text":"Experiment 1","value":"experiment-1","line":18,"column":0},"experiment-2":{"type":"header","text":"Experiment 2","value":"experiment-2","line":26,"column":0}},"fname":"CWF.sim","updated":1636095383581,"created":1636095154775,"parent":"MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"45e793ed476c0ee9c77c7eccc11ba27d","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"cwf-simulation-study\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#cwf-simulation-study\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>CWF Simulation Study</h1>\n<p>Simulation study for covariance weighted forecasting.</p>\n<h2 id=\"motivation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#motivation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Motivation</h2>\n<p>The purpose of this simulation study is to implement very simple forecasting methods on a simple dgp for which we know which ones would perform well, and see how the method works.</p>\n<p>Thus, it acts as a bit of sanity check.</p>\n<p>This is currently just ordered as a bit of a journal (chronologically).</p>\n<h2 id=\"experiment-1\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#experiment-1\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Experiment 1</h2>\n<p>The data is simulated from an AR model, and the constituent models are fixed <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">rho</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">o</span></span></span></span></span> AR models.</p>\n<p>The method did not work with this setup, because the residuals from all constituent models behaved very similarly. </p>\n<p>Hence, this leads to a development of a regularity condition that the residuals of all constituent models cannot be too collinear, as then the covariance matrix will be close to singular and difficult to invert.</p>\n<h2 id=\"experiment-2\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#experiment-2\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Experiment 2</h2>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":451},"end":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":462},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":464},"end":{"line":14,"column":12,"offset":475},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Meeting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"TODO","alias":"TODO","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":477},"end":{"line":16,"column":9,"offset":485},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"TODO"}}],"anchors":{"quick-links":{"type":"header","text":"Quick Links","value":"quick-links","line":17,"column":0}},"fname":"root","updated":1637563604861,"created":159